---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const updated = new Date().toLocaleDateString("en-US", {
	year: "numeric",
	month: "long",
	day: "numeric",
});
const email = "hello@attentivebrain.com";
---

<Layout
	title="Terms & conditions — attentivebrain"
	description="The terms that govern your use of attentivebrain: acceptable use, accounts and leaderboard conduct, intellectual property, and disclaimers."
	keywords="attentivebrain terms and conditions, terms of service, terms of use"
>
	<main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-(--spacing-section)">
		<p class="text-caption text-ink-muted-48 mb-4 uppercase tracking-[0.04em]">Terms &amp; conditions</p>
		<h1 class="text-hero text-ink">Terms of use.</h1>
		<p class="text-caption text-ink-muted-48 mt-4">Last updated {updated}</p>

		<div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-ink-muted-80">
			<p>
				Welcome to attentivebrain. By accessing or using this website and game (the
				"Service"), you agree to these Terms &amp; Conditions. If you do not agree, please
				do not use the Service.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">1. Use of the Service</h2>
			<p>
				attentivebrain is provided free of charge for personal, non-commercial use. You
				may use it for your own focus and memory practice. You agree not to misuse the
				Service — including attempting to disrupt it, access it through automated means
				to gain an unfair leaderboard advantage, or interfere with other people's use.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">2. Accounts</h2>
			<p>
				Signing in is optional and handled through Google. You are responsible for the
				activity that happens under your account. Choose a display name that is not
				offensive, impersonating, or infringing — we reserve the right to remove names,
				photos, or scores that violate these terms or that we reasonably consider
				inappropriate.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">3. Leaderboard conduct</h2>
			<p>
				The leaderboard is meant to be a fair, friendly record of real scores. Submitting
				falsified scores, exploiting bugs, or otherwise manipulating rankings is not
				permitted, and we may remove affected entries at our discretion.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">4. Intellectual property</h2>
			<p>
				The Service, including its design, text, and code, is owned by attentivebrain and
				protected by applicable laws. You may not copy, redistribute, or create
				derivative works from it without permission, except as allowed by law.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">5. Disclaimer</h2>
			<p>
				attentivebrain is a casual training game offered "as is." It is not a medical
				device and does not provide medical, psychological, or diagnostic advice. The
				metrics it reports are for personal interest only. We make no guarantee of any
				particular outcome and do not warrant that the Service will be uninterrupted or
				error-free.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">6. Limitation of liability</h2>
			<p>
				To the fullest extent permitted by law, attentivebrain shall not be liable for
				any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of, or
				inability to use, the Service.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">7. Changes</h2>
			<p>
				We may update these terms as the Service evolves. Continued use after changes
				means you accept the revised terms. The "last updated" date above reflects the
				current version.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">8. Contact</h2>
			<p>
				Questions about these terms? Email us at
				<a href={`mailto:${email}`} class="link-action">{email}</a>.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="mt-12">
			<a href="/" class="btn-primary">Back to the game</a>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>
